## 1. Disk Usage Alert Script

Checks disk usage and sends an alert if it crosses a threshold.

```bash
#!/bin/bash

THRESHOLD=80
EMAIL="admin@example.com"

df -h | grep -vE '^Filesystem|tmpfs|cdrom' | awk '{ print $5 " " $1 }' | while read output;
do
  usage=$(echo $output | awk '{ print $1 }' | cut -d'%' -f1)
  partition=$(echo $output | awk '{ print $2 }')

  if [ $usage -ge $THRESHOLD ]; then
    echo "Warning: Disk usage is at ${usage}% on ${partition}" \
    | mail -s "Disk Alert" $EMAIL
  fi
done
```

💡 **Interview angle:** monitoring, automation, parsing command output, cron jobs.

