## 2. Log Cleanup Script

Deletes logs older than X days.

```bash
#!/bin/bash

LOG_DIR="/var/log/myapp"
DAYS=7

find $LOG_DIR -type f -name "*.log" -mtime +$DAYS -exec rm -f {} \;

echo "Old logs deleted successfully."
```

💡 Shows: housekeeping, `find`, safe file handling.

