## 8. Port Check Script

Checks if a port is open.

```bash
#!/bin/bash

PORT=8080

if netstat -tuln | grep -q ":$PORT "; then
  echo "Port $PORT is in use."
else
  echo "Port $PORT is free."
fi
```

💡 Shows: networking basics.

