# 1. Process Monitoring + Auto Restart (more robust version)

```bash
#!/bin/bash

PROCESS="apache2"

if pgrep -x "$PROCESS" > /dev/null; then
    echo "$PROCESS is running"
else
    echo "$PROCESS is NOT running. Starting it..."
    systemctl start $PROCESS

    if pgrep -x "$PROCESS" > /dev/null; then
        echo "$PROCESS started successfully"
    else
        echo "Failed to start $PROCESS"
    fi
fi
```

### 🔍 Explanation

* `pgrep -x` checks if exact process is running
* If not running → starts service
* Then verifies again (important in production scripts)

### 💡 Interview points

* How you validate service recovery
* Why double-check after restart
* Basic self-healing automation

