# 3. Simple Deployment Script (CI/CD style)

```bash
#!/bin/bash

APP_DIR="/var/www/myapp"

echo "Pulling latest code..."
cd $APP_DIR || exit

git pull origin main

echo "Installing dependencies..."
npm install

echo "Restarting application..."
pm2 restart all

echo "Deployment completed successfully"
```

### 🔍 Explanation

* Automates deployment steps
* Pull → install → restart
* Very common in small CI/CD pipelines

### 💡 Interview points

* What happens if `git pull` fails?
* How to rollback?
* How CI/CD tools improve this (Jenkins, GitHub Actions)

