# 6. File Backup with Rotation (important concept)

```bash
#!/bin/bash

SOURCE="/home/user/data"
BACKUP_DIR="/home/user/backups"

mkdir -p $BACKUP_DIR

tar -czf $BACKUP_DIR/backup-$(date +%F).tar.gz $SOURCE

# Keep only last 5 backups
cd $BACKUP_DIR || exit
ls -tp | grep -v '/$' | tail -n +6 | xargs -I {} rm -- {}
```

### 🔍 Explanation

* Creates daily backup
* Keeps only last 5 backups (rotation policy)

### 💡 Interview points

* Why log/backup rotation is needed
* Prevents disk overflow
* Real production requirement

