# 7. SSH Connectivity Check Script

```bash
#!/bin/bash

HOST="192.168.1.10"

ping -c 2 $HOST > /dev/null

if [ $? -eq 0 ]; then
    echo "Host is reachable"
else
    echo "Host is NOT reachable"
fi
```

### 🔍 Explanation

* Uses ping to test network connectivity
* `$?` checks exit status of last command

### 💡 Interview points

* Exit codes in Linux
* Basic networking troubleshooting

